<sec id="sec2dot3dot5-ijerph-16-00692" class="sec">
 <div class="title" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">2.3.5. Climatic Tendency</div>
 <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">The climatic tendency of CH
  <sub>4</sub> fluxes is expressed by a linear equation by using the least square method. The formulas is as follows:
  <div id="FD3-ijerph-16-00692" class="disp-formula">
   <span class="label">(3)</span>
   <div id="mm4" class="math">
    <div class="mrow">
     <div class="mrow">
      <div class="msub">
       <div accent="true" class="mover">
        <span class="mi">Y</span>
        <span class="mo">^</span>
       </div>
       <span class="mi">i</span>
      </div>
      <span class="mo">=</span>
      <span class="mi">a</span>
      <span class="mi">t</span>
      <span class="mo">+</span>
      <span class="mi">b</span>
     </div>
    </div>
   </div>
  </div> where 
  <div class="inline-formula">
   <div id="mm5" class="math">
    <div class="mrow">
     <div class="mrow">
      <div class="msub">
       <div class="mrow">
        <div class="mover">
         <span class="mi">Y</span>
         <span class="mo">^</span>
        </div>
       </div>
       <span class="mi">i</span>
      </div>
     </div>
    </div>
   </div>
  </div> is the fitting value of CH
  <sub>4</sub> fluxes, 
  <span class="italic">t</span> is the corresponding year, and 
  <span class="italic">a</span> and 
  <span class="italic">b</span> are the regression coefficients.
 </p>
 <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
  <span class="italic">a</span> Ã— 10 is the climatic tendency, which represents the change rate of CH
  <sub>4</sub> fluxes every 10 years (10a). The positive value indicates an increasing trend, while the negative value indicates a decreasing trend.
 </p>
